Five people suffered serious injuries when a package received at a residence in Stephen Dlamini Road exploded earlier today, Berea Mail reports. According to Captain Poobalan Naidoo from Berea police, a package was received at the premises this afternoon and was opened by one person in the lounge. The package exploded, injuring five people present. Police are on scene, he said. READ MORE: Randburg Square receives false bomb alarm Garrith Jamieson from Rescue Care Paramedics said the five seriously injured people were taken to hospital for further care. The events leading up to the explosion are unknown at present. The bomb squad is on scene, and police are investigating, he said. More news to follow. READ MORE: Randburg Square receives false bomb alarm Caxton News Service For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.